t\n1229\t0\n1230\t\n1231\t100\n1232\t\n1233\t200\n1234\t\n1235\t300\n1236\t\n1237\t400\n1238\t\n1239\t500\n1240\t\n1241\tFig. 1. Causal FRN block replay improves after the first completed block\n1242\tand remains stable over time. Curves show per-window metric deltas relative\n1243\tto frozen FRN on LibriSpeech-40 speaker files; shaded bands denote ± one\n1244\tstandard error. The first 30 s block is shaded because no replay has fired\n1245\tyet, so the output matches the frozen baseline. Dotted vertical lines mark\n1246\tsubsequent 30 s block boundaries; each completed block is replayed for six\n1247\tself-supervised epochs before updating the weights for future blocks.\n1248\t\n1249\tand the selected checkpoint can then be used for concealment.\n1250\tMulti-epoch adaptation multiplies the adaptation cost by the\n1251\tnumber of epochs; five epochs correspond to approximately\n1252\treal-time factor 15. This tradeoff is appropriate for offline\n1253\trestoration or quality-oriented processing, while lower update\n1254\trates are a natural direction for real-time deployment.\n1255\t7) No-leak verification: The no-leak constraint is enforced\n1256\tin both the data split and the loss computation. The held-out set\n1257\tH is sampled only from observed packets and is never used\n1258\tfor gradient updates. At the start of each epoch, the output\n1259\tbuffer is re-zeroed at the true loss positions L. When a true lost\n1260\tpacket is encountered, the buffer receives the model prediction,\n1261\t\n1262\tpkt-NMSE↓ Mel-SC↓ PEAQ↑ PLCMOS↑\n1263\t\n1264\tnever the clean target audio. In addition, the supervised 80sample look-ahead region is masked out wherever it overlaps\n1265\ta true lost packet, so clean samples from L cannot enter either\n1266\tthe MSE or MR-STFT loss.\n1267\tWe verify this implementation with a bit-exact canary\n1268\ttest. In the canary run, all clean audio samples at true lost\n1269\tpositions are replaced with loud noise before retraining. Under\n1270\tsingle-threaded deterministic execution, the adapted weights\n1271\tand the complete validation trajectory are byte-identical to\n1272\tthe clean-audio run through five epochs. The clean-versusclean nondeterminism floor and the clean-versus-corruptedloss signal are both exactly zero. This confirms that clean audio\n1273\tat true lost positions has no path into training, validation, or\n1274\tmodel selection.\n1275\t\n1276\t\f10\n1277\t\n1278\tIEEE/ACM TRANSACTIONS ON AUDIO, SPEECH, AND LANGUAGE PROCESSING\n1279\t\n1280\tTABLE V\n1281\tPARC NET RESULTS ON IN - DISTRIBUTION MAESTRO SOLO PIANO ,\n1282\t50- MINUTE FILE ( SINGLE FILE PER LOSS RATE ). PKT-NMSE AND M EL -SC\n1283\tARE LOWER - BETTER ; PEAQ ODG AND PLCMOS ARE HIGHER - BETTER .\n1284\tPLR Method\n1285\t\n1286\tpkt-NMSE↓ Mel-SC↓ PEAQ↑ PLCMOS↑\n1287\t\n1288\tZero-fill\n1289\tFrozen\n1290\tCausal best-val (ours)\n1291\t0.10\n1292\tTwo-pass best-val (ours)\n1293\tOracle (single-pass UB)\n1294\tMulti-epoch (ours)\n1295\t\n1296\t+0.00\n1297\t−5.28\n1298\t−5.52\n1299\t−5.59\n1300\t−5.61\n1301\t−5.94\n1302\t\n1303\t0.2410\n1304\t0.1356\n1305\t0.1348\n1306\t0.1328\n1307\t0.1324\n1308\t0.1268\n1309\t\n1310\t−3.88\n1311\t−2.32\n1312\t−2.44\n1313\t−2.39\n1314\t−2.45\n1315\t−2.36\n1316\t\n1317\t1.18\n1318\t1.32\n1319\t1.33\n1320\t1.32\n1321\t1.33\n1322\t1.34\n1323\t\n1324\tZero-fill\n1325\tFrozen\n1326\tCausal best-val (ours)\n1327\t0.20\n1328\tTwo-pass best-val (ours)\n1329\tOracle (single-pass UB)\n1330\tMulti-epoch (ours)\n1331\t\n1332\t+0.00\n1333\t−4.92\n1334\t−5.12\n1335\t−5.08\n1336\t−5.23\n1337\t−5.49\n1338\t\n1339\t0.3404\n1340\t0.1974\n1341\t0.1961\n1342\t0.1956\n1343\t0.1965\n1344\t0.1867\n1345\t\n1346\t−3.78\n1347\t−3.51\n1348\t−3.55\n1349\t−3.54\n1350\t−3.56\n1351\t−3.55\n1352\t\n1353\t1.17\n1354\t1.29\n1355\t1.30\n1356\t1.29\n1357\t1.30\n1358\t1.32\n1359\t\n1360\tZero-fill\n1361\tFrozen\n1362\tCausal best-val (ours)\n1363\t0.30\n1364\tTwo-pass best-val (ours)\n1365\tOracle (single-pass UB)\n1366\tMulti-